President Trump has declared a major disaster in the state of New Jersey and authorized federal assistance to support the state's recovery efforts in response to the COVID-19 pandemic. This declaration makes federal funding available for crisis counseling and emergency protective measures, including direct federal assistance. The Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) has appointed Robert Little III as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made based on future assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.